<title>ITALY: Italy's Palermo sees August CPI at 2.5 pct yr/yr.</title>
<headline>Italy's Palermo sees August CPI at 2.5 pct yr/yr.</headline>
<dateline>PALERMO, Italy 1996-08-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Italian city of Palermo said its August consumer price index stood at +0.1 percent month-on-month and +2.5 percent year-on-year.</p>
<p>In July, Palermo's month-on-month inflation rate fell 0.3 percent but rose year-on-year 2.4 percent.</p>
<p>The city's CPI has a weighting of 6.80 percent on the national index. The 10 sample cities have a combined weighting of 69.67 percent on the total index.  </p>
<p>Following is the breakdown of the price changes.</p>
<p>(figures in brackets refer to July 1996):</p>
<p>					    Month/Month     Year/Year</p>
<p>    General index		     0.1   (-0.3)    2.5  (2.4)</p>
<p>    Food				  0.1    (0.1)    4.8  (4.5)</p>
<p>    Clothing and footwear	   0.0    (0.0)    3.4  (3.4)</p>
<p>    Housing and utility charges   0.5   (-3.6)   -0.2 (-0.7)</p>
<p>    Furniture			   0.3   (-0.3     2.3  (2.0)</p>
<p>    Health services		   0.0   (-0.4)    2.2  (2.0)</p>
<p>    Transportation		    0.1   (-0.1)    3.3  (3.1)</p>
<p>    Entertainment and culture     0.1    (0.0)    0.1  (0.5)</p>
<p>    Education			   0.0    (0.0)    5.6  (5.6)</p>
<p>    Hotels and restaurants	  0.0    (0.3)    2.2  (2.2)</p>
<p>    Other goods or services	 0.0    (0.0)    0.0  (0.0)</p>
<p>-- Milan newsroom ++392 66129526</p>
